<reg_short_dscr>:
Controls automatic learn limits
------------------------------
<reg_public_text>:
Per FID configuration of autolearn limits
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
Set if specified MAX learn cnt limit is exceeded and max learn cnt was enabled. Write '1' to clear this field.
------------------------------
<field_enc>:
0: Learn cnt not exceeded.
1: Learning operation has failed due to FID max learn cnt exceeded.
Write '1' to clear this field.
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
Contains the number of MAC table entries currently learned associated with a given FID.
------------------------------
<field_enc>:
0 : no entries
------------------------------
<reg_short_dscr>:
Controls automatic learn limits per FID
------------------------------
<reg_public_text>:
Per FID configuration of MAC table learn limits
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
Allow setting FID_LIMIT_INTR when exceeding limit on learning (happens when MAC address are supposed to be installed in the MAC table).
------------------------------
<field_enc>:
0: Disable 
1: allow FID_LIMIT_INTR to be set upon trying to learn a MAC address that causes learn limit to be exceeded
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
Action for traffic when learn limit is exceeded.
------------------------------
<field_enc>:
00: Normal forward
01: Enable redirection to CPU queue
10: Enable copy to CPU queue
11: Discard the frame
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
Configures the number of MAC table entries that can be used for a given FID (through Automatic learning and CPU based learning with LOCK bit cleared and not multicast).
------------------------------
<field_enc>:
0: Disable i.e. no learn limit for the FID
1: Only learning of one MAC address allowed for this FID
...
n: Learning of n MAC address allowed for this FID
------------------------------
